title: Dizmas-Tension
description:
Dizmas is a Christian rock band from Lancaster in Southern California.

Nick, Clayton, and brothers Zach and Josh began playing together in 1998 as teenagers while attending Desert Christian High School. They were later joined by Jon, who is from Mechanicsburg, Pennsylvania. Their debut album "On a Search in America" was released on June 21, 2005. Jon's younger brother, Joey, joined Dizmas as a roadie/merch guy/techie in 2006, now serving as tour manager. On May 03, 2006 their song "Revolution" aired on NY - Season 2: Stealing Home.[2] Their second album "Tension" was produced by Steve Wilson and released on May 05, 2007. On July 10, 2007 their song "Shake It Off" aired on ESPN. Soon after their hit single "Play It Safe" reached #1 on Radio & Records Christian Rock National Airplay chart of national broadcasters in the United States for the week ending Aug 03, 2007.
